  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "I deleted my friend ID from WeChat. How do I find it again?",
  "response": "If you've deleted a friend's ID from WeChat and want to reconnect, don't worry\u2014there are several methods you can try to find and re-add them. Here's a comprehensive guide to help you retrieve your friend's WeChat contact:\n\n### 1. **Search by WeChat ID or Other Identifiers**\n- **Open WeChat** and navigate to the **\"Contacts\"** tab.\n- Tap the **\"+\"** icon (usually located at the top right corner) and select **\"Add Contacts.\"**\n- Choose **\"WeChat ID\"**, **\"Phone Number\"**, **\"Email\"**, or **\"QQ Number\"** (if applicable) and enter your friend's information to search for them.\n\n### 2. **Use Your Phone\u2019s Contacts**\n- **Ensure** that your friend's phone number is saved in your device's **contacts list**.\n- In WeChat, go to **\"Add Contacts\"** and select **\"Mobile Contacts.\"**\n- WeChat will sync with your phone contacts and display any matching profiles. You can then add them back as a friend.\n\n### 3. **Scan Their QR Code**\n- If you **previously saved** your friend's WeChat QR code or they can provide it again:\n  - In WeChat, tap the **\"+\"** icon and select **\"Scan QR Code.\"**\n  - Use your phone's camera to scan their QR code, which will allow you to add them directly.\n\n### 4. **Use the \"People Nearby\" Feature**\n- If you and your friend are in the **same location**, you can use the **\"People Nearby\"** feature:\n  - Go to **\"Add Contacts\"** > **\"People Nearby.\"**\n  - Browse through the list to find your friend and send a friend request.\n\n### 5. **Check Previous Chat History**\n- If you **had previous conversations** with your friend:\n  - Open WeChat and go to the **\"Chats\"** tab.\n  - Find the old chat with your friend. Even if you've deleted them, the chat history might still be there.\n  - Tap on their name in the chat header, and you may find an option to **re-add** them as a contact.\n\n### 6. **Ask a Mutual Friend**\n- If you have **mutual friends** on WeChat:\n  - Ask one of them to **share your contact** with your friend or to **send an invitation** to reconnect.\n\n### 7. **Find Through Other Social Media Platforms**\n- If you're connected on platforms like **Facebook**, **Instagram**, or **LinkedIn**:\n  - Check their profiles for their WeChat ID or contact details.\n  - Reach out to them on these platforms to request their WeChat information.\n\n### 8. **Direct Communication Outside WeChat**\n- **Email** or **SMS** your friend directly if you have another way to contact them:\n  - Ask them to **send you their WeChat ID** or **QR code** again.\n\n### 9. **Check WeChat Backups**\n- If you **regularly back up** your WeChat data (using WeChat's built-in backup feature or third-party services):\n  - You might be able to **restore your contacts** from a previous backup that includes your friend.\n\n### 10. **Contact WeChat Support**\n- If all else fails, consider reaching out to **WeChat Support**:\n  - While they may not be able to provide your friend's contact information directly due to privacy policies, they might offer additional solutions or guidance.\n\n### **Prevention Tips for the Future**\n- **Regularly Back Up Contacts**: Use WeChat\u2019s backup feature or sync your contacts with your phone to prevent accidental loss.\n- **Save QR Codes**: Keep a screenshot or note of your most frequently used contacts\u2019 QR codes for easy re-addition.\n- **Maintain Multiple Contact Points**: Besides WeChat, keep contact information on other platforms or via email.\n\n### **Important Considerations**\n- **Privacy**: Respect your friend\u2019s privacy when attempting to reconnect. Ensure that your methods comply with WeChat\u2019s terms of service and privacy guidelines.\n- **Mutual Consent**: Re-adding someone should be done with their consent to maintain a positive relationship.\n\nBy following these steps, you should be able to locate and re-add your friend on WeChat. If you encounter any specific issues during the process, feel free to provide more details, and I can offer further assistance!",
